<subSubSection id="41F5655DFFE5D932FF48FEA9FE76FC18" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" type="description">
<paragraph id="095036D6FFE5D932FF48FEA9FDC2FE87" blockId="4.[151,1436,260,1187]" box="[151,554,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="3B9BEAC4FFE5D932FF48FEA9FEC1FE86" bold="true" box="[151,297,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Description.</emphasis>
Length. Male 4.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="095036D6FFE5D932FF18FE8AFC2DFE37" blockId="4.[151,1436,260,1187]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="3B9BEAC4FFE5D932FF18FE8AFEA1FEDB" box="[199,329,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body yellow brown (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FD9DFE8AFD64FEDB" box="[578,652,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,205,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1408,195,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. (P.) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Body, dorsal view; B, Habitus, lateral view; C, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, Face. P. (P.) dentiforma sp. nov. E, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; F, Face; G, Body, dorsal view; H, Habitus, lateral view. P. (P.) dinghuensis sp. nov. I, Body, dorsal view; J, Habitus, lateral view; K, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; L, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225937/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Figs. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FD5DFE85FD64FEDB" box="[642,652,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). Head and face yellow. Ocelli brown, surrounding area yellow, eyes red brown (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FEBBFEE1FE42FEFF" box="[356,426,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,205,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1408,195,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. (P.) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Body, dorsal view; B, Habitus, lateral view; C, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, Face. P. (P.) dentiforma sp. nov. E, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; F, Face; G, Body, dorsal view; H, Habitus, lateral view. P. (P.) dinghuensis sp. nov. I, Body, dorsal view; J, Habitus, lateral view; K, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; L, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225937/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Fig. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FE40FEE1FE42FEFF" box="[415,426,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Pronotum pale yellow, with dense oblique striations. Scutellum ochraceous with numerous dark brown and pale brown spots (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FD4BFEC2FD3CFE13" box="[660,724,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,205,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1408,195,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. (P.) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Body, dorsal view; B, Habitus, lateral view; C, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, Face. P. (P.) dentiforma sp. nov. E, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; F, Face; G, Body, dorsal view; H, Habitus, lateral view. P. (P.) dinghuensis sp. nov. I, Body, dorsal view; J, Habitus, lateral view; K, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; L, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225937/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Fig. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FD16FEDDFD3CFE13" box="[713,724,368,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Forewings yellow brown, much darker basally and distally, middle section hyaline. Venation dark yellow with white spots (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FCBFFE39FC77FE37" box="[864,927,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,205,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1408,195,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. (P.) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Body, dorsal view; B, Habitus, lateral view; C, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, Face. P. (P.) dentiforma sp. nov. E, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; F, Face; G, Body, dorsal view; H, Habitus, lateral view. P. (P.) dinghuensis sp. nov. I, Body, dorsal view; J, Habitus, lateral view; K, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; L, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225937/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Fig. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FC4BFE39FC77FE37" box="[916,927,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="095036D6FFE5D932FF18FE1AFED6FE6E" blockId="4.[151,1436,260,1187]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="3B9BEAC4FFE5D932FF18FE1AFEBFFE4B" box="[199,343,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Morphology.</emphasis>
Body stout. Face slightly convex in lateral view. Eyes slightly prominent. 
<collectingCountry id="71F87646FFE5D932FB7DFE1AFB32FE4B" box="[1186,1242,439,464]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial chaetotaxy R 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FF76FE46FF58FE62" box="[169,176,491,505]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="1.0">1</number>
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FF6FFE71FF25FE6F" box="[176,205,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="11.0">11</number>
, R 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FF33FE46FF1CFE62" box="[236,244,491,505]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="2.0">2</number>
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FF2BFE71FEEBFE6F" box="[244,259,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="8.0">8</number>
, R 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FEFDFE46FEC2FE62" box="[290,298,491,505]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="3.0">3</number>
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FEF5FE71FED2FE6E" box="[298,314,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="5.0">5</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="095036D6FFE5D932FF18FDAFFCF3FCC4" blockId="4.[151,1436,260,1187]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="3B9BEAC4FFE5D932FF18FDAFFE9EFD80" box="[199,374,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FE33FDAFFDDAFD80" box="[492,562,514,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[222,1363,201,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1913]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pedionis (Pedionis) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, ventral view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225938/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Fig. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FDFBFDAEFDDAFD80" box="[548,562,515,539]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A) broad, slightly concave on dorsal margin. Apex with 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FB13FDAEFB32FD80" box="[1228,1242,515,539]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="3.0">3</number>
obtuse dendritic processes in lateral view, producing several strong setae on caudoventral margin. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FB3AFD8BFACFFDA4" box="[1253,1319,550,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[222,1363,201,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1913]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pedionis (Pedionis) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, ventral view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225938/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Fig. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FAC6FD8AFACFFDA4" box="[1305,1319,551,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A) slender with many marginal setae, apex stout. Style (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FD7CFDE7FD00FDF8" box="[675,744,586,611]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[222,1363,201,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1913]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pedionis (Pedionis) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, ventral view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225938/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Fig. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FD05FDE6FD00FDF8" box="[730,744,587,611]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
G) parallel-margined and angled on apical third, some stout setae produced at this broad margin. The apex dorsally upturned and truncate, producing several setae on dorsal margin. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FEAAFD3FFE2EFD30" box="[373,454,658,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[222,1363,201,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1913]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pedionis (Pedionis) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, ventral view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225938/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Figs. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FE68FD3EFE2EFD30" box="[439,454,659,683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D, E) broader basally, shaft strongly sinuated, angled heavily on apical third and with bulge occurred in mid-dorsum in lateral view; apex tapering, and with two pairs of processes, the apical process located at lateral margin, subapical finger-like lamellate protrusion located on ventral margin. Connective (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FABBFD77FF4EFC8C" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[222,1363,201,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1913]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pedionis (Pedionis) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, ventral view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225938/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Figs. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FF48FD52FF4EFC8C" box="[151,166,767,791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B, C) broadened basally, finger-like protrusion in middle near apex, both sides bent to inside. Dorsal connective (
<figureCitation id="91D42A53FFE5D932FF40FC8FFF0DFCA0" box="[159,229,802,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[222,1363,201,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1913]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pedionis (Pedionis) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, ventral view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225938/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Fig. 
<number id="BF2724F1FFE5D932FF08FC8EFF0DFCA0" box="[215,229,803,827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
F) with broad base, a ventral curved and a median caudally-directed processes, the latter with minutely serrated margin and produced into two obvious bendings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="095036D6FFE5D932FF18FCC7FE76FC18" blockId="4.[151,1436,260,1187]" box="[199,414,874,899]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="3B9BEAC4FFE5D932FF18FCC7FECAFC18" box="[199,290,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
